# Cursor Workflow Rules — Volant

## Cursor's Domain (do these in Cursor)

- Writing and editing code inside `platform/`
- Implementing components from specs in `Plans/slice-1-fleet-overview.md`
- CSS / styling iteration
- Refactoring existing code
- Debugging runtime errors
- Autocomplete-heavy boilerplate (package.json, docker-compose, config files)
- Running local dev servers and verifying exit criteria

## Claude Code's Domain (don't duplicate — let Claude Code handle)

- Planning and architecture decisions
- Writing to the Obsidian vault (Sessions/, Plans/, Strategy/, etc.)
- Research (Exa MCP, web search)
- Email and outreach drafts
- Git commits and pushes
- Session logs
- Task list updates
- Prompt engineering for pitch decks / investor materials

## Handoff Protocol

1. Claude Code writes the task to `CURSOR_TASKS.md` (repo root)
2. Cursor reads `CURSOR_TASKS.md` for what to build
3. Cursor implements, verifies exit criteria via terminal
4. When done: mark step complete in `CURSOR_TASKS.md` (add ✅ and notes)
5. Claude Code picks up completion next session, updates `Plans/Task List.md`

## Code Quality Rules

- No TypeScript — plain JS for now (speed > correctness at prototype stage)
- No hardcoded colors — always import from `src/design/tokens.js`
- No `console.log` spam — one startup log per service ("PostgreSQL connected", "Redis connected")
- CSS: CSS custom properties fed from tokens.js — no Tailwind, no inline styles
- Comments only when WHY is non-obvious — no "this function does X" comments
